<paragraph id="3A4B5872932BFFBCCDD68004FEFCFCBD" blockId="4.[151,929,749,808]" box="[151,309,783,808]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
(
<figureCitation id="A2CF44F7932BFFBCCDDE8004FECDFCBD" box="[159,260,783,808]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 22" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1821,1843]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,197,1799]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1799]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 22. Species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 1 – 2. A. alstonii. 3 – 4. A. nurtia ludibunda. 5 – 6. A. pulchra. 7 – 8. A. bonita. 9 – 10. A. amalfreda. 11 – 12. A. physis phyton. 13 – 14. A. halli sp. nov. holotype. 15 – 16. A. celata. 17 – 20. A. gallardi sp. nov. 17 – 18. Male holotype. 19 – 20. Female (tentative determination). 21 – 22. A. aparamilla. Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233289/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
Figs 
<number id="8C3C4A55932BFFBCCD96801BFECDFCBD" box="[215,260,784,808]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="3.735" valueMax="4.47" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A2CF44F7932BFFBCCC4E801BFEE5FCBD" box="[271,300,784,808]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 55" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1704,1726]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1682]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[152,1434,193,1683]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 55. Male genitalia of species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 46. A. alstonii. 47. A. nurtia ludibunda. 48. A. pulchra. 49. A. bonita. 50. A. amalfreda. 51. A. physis phyton. 52. A. halli sp. nov. paratype. 53. A. celata. 54. A. gallardi sp. nov. paratype from PNSD. 55. A. aparamilla. Left to right: dorsal view of uncus, lateral view of tegumen, saccus, uncus, gnathos, valva and aedeagus, and ventral view of valva. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233292/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">47</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A4B5872932BFFBCCDD68053FC01FBDD" blockId="4.[151,1436,855,1096]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
In 
<number id="8C3C4A55932BFFBCCDF98053FF39FCE5" box="[184,240,856,880]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="2013.0">2013</number>
three males were collected exhibiting hilltoping behavior one meter from the ground around 
<number id="8C3C4A55932BFFBCC866805CFA8AFCE5" box="[1319,1347,855,880]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="15.0">15</number>
:00h. In 
<number id="8C3C4A55932BFFBCCDD68077FF06FC01" box="[151,207,892,916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="2014.0">2014</number>
more three specimens were collected exhibiting the same behavior and at the same time observed on 
<number id="8C3C4A55932BFFBCC8038077FAB7FC01" box="[1346,1406,892,916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="2013.0">2013</number>
. The specimens from 
<collectionCode id="5CE5C0B7932BFFBCCCC080ABFE00FC2D" box="[385,457,928,952]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">PNSD</collectionCode>
are more similar to the 
<typeStatus id="E54FE6D0932BFFBCCF9380ABFCCBFC2D" box="[722,770,928,952]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="FDF423F1932BFFBCCE6680ABFAF5FC2D" authority="Brevignon &amp; Gallard, 1995" authorityName="Brevignon &amp; Gallard" authorityYear="1995" box="[807,1340,927,952]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nurtia" subSpecies="ludibunda">
<emphasis id="08808460932BFFBCCE6680ABFBCAFC2D" box="[807,1027,927,952]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. nurtia ludibunda</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5E652583932BFFBCC9488094FAF5FC2D" author="Brevignon" box="[1033,1340,927,952]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" refString="Brevignon, C. &amp; Gallard, J. - Y. (1995) Contribuition a l'etude des Riodinidae de Guyane Francaise. Le genre Argyrogrammana Strand, 1932. Lambillionea, 95, 393 - 406." type="journal article" year="1995">
Brévignon &amp; Gallard, 
<number id="8C3C4A55932BFFBCC8458094FAF5FC2D" box="[1284,1340,927,952]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
than the nominative subspecies. They differ from the latter by the reduced orange markings, blue patch thinner on the forewing upperside, and the reduced blue markings in both wings underside. Specimens from 
<collectionCode id="5CE5C0B7932BFFBCC98C80E3FADDFB95" box="[1229,1300,1000,1024]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">PNSD</collectionCode>
are slightly different of the 
<typeStatus id="E54FE6D0932BFFBCCC0D8707FE67FBB0" box="[332,430,1036,1061]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="FDF423F1932BFFBCCC998707FD70FBB0" box="[472,697,1036,1061]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nurtia" subSpecies="ludibunda">
<emphasis id="08808460932BFFBCCC998707FD70FBB0" box="[472,697,1036,1061]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. nurtia ludibunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in size and shape of the blue patch of forewing upperside, even though, no differences were observed in the morphology of the genitalia.
</paragraph>
